{"word":"H3665 - כָּנַע - kânaʻ - kaw-nah' - Bring down","slug":"H3665","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">כָּנַע</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>kânaʻ"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>kaw-nah'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Bring down"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05DB;&#x05BC;&#x05E0;&#x05E2; - ka&#x0302;na&#x201B;</b> - <i>kaw-nah'</i><p/>A primitive root; properly to <i>bend</i> the knee; hence to <i>humiliate</i>, <i>vanquish: - </i>bring down (low), into subjection, under, humble (self), subdue."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3666\">H3666</a>, <a href=\"#/H3667\">H3667</a>, <a href=\"#/H3668\">H3668</a>, <a href=\"#/H3669\">H3669</a>"}]}